        <p id="text.istoric">Back on September 9, 1947, Grace Hopper, a Harvard computer scientist, was running tests on
            a calculator and
            found calculation errors. She did some investigation and found a moth that had landed between two solenoid
            contacts, shorting out an electromechanical relay. Apparently, the bug had been attracted by the warmth of
            the machine.</p>
