        <br>
        <div id="RequirementAnalysis">
            <br>
            <h1>Requirement Analysis</h1>
            <br>
            <h2>Why?</h2>
            <br>
            <p> To understand the product requirements, what the client wants</p>
            <p>To raise any requirements inconsistencies as soon as possible</p>
            <p>To refine the scope of testing</p>
            <br>
            <h2>How?</h2>
            <br>
            <p>The requirements are read and analyzed</p>
            <p>Clarify all requirements documents</p>
            <br>
        </div>
        <div id="TestPlanning">
            <br>
            <h1>Test Planning</h1>
            <br>
            <h2>Why?</h2>
            <br>
            <p>To describe the test strategy, objectives, schedule, estimation, deliverables, and resources required to
                perform testing for a software product</p>
            <p>It helps us determine the effort needed to validate the quality of the application under test</p>
            <p>Also serves as a blueprint to conduct software testing activities as a defined process, which is minutely
                monitored and controlled by the test manager.</p>
            <br>
            <h2>How?</h2>
            <br>
            <p>Analyze the product</p>
            <p>Design the Test Strategy</p>
            <p>Define the Test Objectives</p>
            <p>Define Test Criteria</p>
            <p>Resource Planning</p>
            <p>Plan Test Environment</p>
            <p>Schedule & Estimation</p>
            <p>Determine Test Deliverables</p>
            <br>
        </div>
        <div id="TestAnalysisandDesign">
            <br>
            <h1>Test Analysis and Design</h1>
            <br>
            <h2>Why</h2>
            <br>
            <p>Prepare all activities needed to be performed in order to be able to execute the actual testing</p>
            <p>Analyse what to test</p>
            <p>Design how to test</p>
            <br>
            <h2>How?</h2>
            <br>
            <p>Review in more details the requirements or other input in order to identify what needs to be tested</p>
            <p>Create, review, update the tests</p>
            <p>Create / Identify / Update the data to test with</p>
            <p>Identify/set/configure the environments where to test</p>
            <br>
        </div>
        <div id="TestExecution">
            <br>
            <h1>Test Execution</h1>
            <br>
            <h2>Which activities have been covered?</h2>
            <br>
            <p>Report bug</p>
            <p>Run test cases</p>
            <p>Exploratory testing</p>
            <br>
            <h2>Which testing types have been covered?</h2>
            <p>Black-box and white-box testing</p>
            <p>Functional and Non-functional testing</p>
            <p>Manual and Automated testing</p>
            <p>Analyze results</p>
            <p>Dynamic and Static testing</p>
            <br>
        </div>
        <div id="TestReporting">
            <br>
            <h1>Test Reporting</h1>
            <br>
            <h2>What?</h2>
            <p>The primary test deliverable from the test execution phase</p>
            <p>Assess the test execution results against the proposed quality measures</p>
            <br>
            <h2>Why?</h2>
            <p>Created for stakeholders to know the quality status of the product under test and
                to make further decisions</p>
            <br>
            <h2>How?</h2>
            <br>
            <p>Evaluate the test results</p>
            <p>Review existing opened defects</p>
            <p>Provide recommendations if the product can / cannot be sent to the client</p>
            <p>Create test reports for stakeholders as agreed</p>
            <br>
        </div>
        <div id="TestClosure">
            <br>
            <h1>Test Closure</h1>
            <br>
            <h2>What are test closure activities?</h2>
            <p>Checking for completion of tests</p>
            <p>Handing over test objects</p>
            <p>Learning Experience</p>
            <p>Archiving</p>
            <br>
        </div>
